

VC++ related stuff
===================

Visual Studio 2017 

Installation
==============
Link: https://devblogs.microsoft.com/cppblog/getting-started-with-visual-studio-for-c-and-cpp-development/

Community Edition is free for personal use.

Install the following components
---------------------------------
- select "Desktop development with C++"
- Optional: VC++2017 toolset
		Just-in-Time debugger
		C++ profiling tools
		Windows 10 SDK
		Visual C++ tools for CMake


Building the Application
========================
Open "Visual Studio 2017" from Windows Menu
1. File -> New Project -> with "VC ++ select", choose "Console App"
2. Give a name for the project
3. By Default it stores the files in C:\Users\<id>\source\repos

After you write some code or use the same code that is generated in IDE
  std::cout << "Hello World!\n"

Go to "Build"


